1 purp ose is to elicit responses on sexual behavior or attitudes shall
2 be available through the superintendent or a designee of the school
3 district for inspection by parents and guardians of the student who
4 will be involved with the class, program or test, survey or
5 questionnaire. Such curriculum, materials, classes, programs,
6 tests, surveys or questionnaires shall include information about
7 consent and shall have as one of its primary purposes the teaching
8 of or informing students about the practice of abstinence. For the
9 purposes of this section, "consent" shall have the same meaning as
10 that provided by Section 113 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
11 The superintendent or a designee of the school district shall
12 provide prior written notification to the parents or guardians of
13 the students involved of their right to inspect the curriculum and
14 material and of their obligation to notify the school in writing if
15 they do not want their child to participate in the class, program,
16 test, survey or questionnaire. Each local board of education shall
17 determine the means of providing written notification to the parents
18 and guardian which will ensure effective notice in an efficient and
19 appropriate manner. No student shall be required to participate in
20 a sex education class or program which discusses sexual behavior or
21 attitudes if unless a parent or guardian of the student objects
22 provides permission in writing to such participation. If the type
23 of program referred to in this section is a part of or is taught
24 during a credit course, a student may be required to enroll in the
