1 cour se but shall not be required to receive instruction in or
2 participate in the program if unless a parent or guardian objects
3 provides permission in writing.
4 B. The superintendent or a designee of a school district in
5 which sex education is taught or a program is offered which is
6 designed for the exclusive purpose of discussing sexual behavior or
7 attitudes shall approve all curriculum and materials which will be
8 used for such education and any test, survey or questionnaire whose
9 primary purpose is to elicit responses on sexual behavior or
10 attitudes used in the school prior to their use in the classroom or
11 school. The teacher involved in the class, program, testing or
12 survey shall submit the curriculum, materials, tests or surveys to
13 the superintendent or a designee for approval prior to their use in
14 the classroom or school. This section shall not apply to those
15 students enrolled in classes, programs, testings or surveys offered
16 through an alternative education program.
17 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 24-158, as
18 amended by Section 2, Chapter 281, O.S.L. 2022 (70 O.S. Supp. 2024,
19 Section 24-158), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 24-158. A. The "Oklahoma Prevention Needs Assessment
21 Survey" means the biennial mental health prevention survey of public
22 school students in grades six, eight, ten, and twelve managed by the
23 Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services.
24
Req. No. 11794 Page 3

1 B. Beginning in the 2022-2023 school year, and biennially
2 thereafter, public schools shall administer the Oklahoma Prevention
3 Needs Assessment Survey, or an alternative survey as provided in
4 subsection D of this section, to students who have parent permission
5 to participate, for the purpose of providing direction to schools,
6 school districts, and communities to effectively improve the lives
7 of students regarding a variety of issues with a focus on alcohol,
8 tobacco, other drug use, mental health, academic failure, and
9 violence.
10 C. The Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services
11 shall maintain the Oklahoma Prevention Needs Assessment Survey and
12 shall provide technical assistance for schools in survey
13 administration, reporting, planning, and development of school
14 mental health prevention and intervention strategies informed by the
15 survey results.
16 D. If a school or school district chooses to administer an
17 alternative survey or assessment tool to fulfill the purpose
18 described in subsection B of this section, it may apply for a waiver
19 through the Department of Mental Health and Substance Abuse
20 Services.
21 E. The school district superintendent or his or her designee
22 shall provide prior written notification to the parents or legal
23 guardians of students to be administered of the intent to administer
24 the Oklahoma Prevention Needs Assessment Survey or an alternative
Req. No. 11794 Page 4

1 surv ey or assessment tool adopted pursuant to subsection D of this
2 section. The notification shall include information to parents and
3 legal guardians that they may must opt their student out of in to
4 the survey or assessment tool by providing written notice to the
5 school district, if they wish for their student to participate.
6 F. Prior to the biennial administration of the Oklahoma
7 Prevention Needs Assessment Survey, the Department of Mental Health
8 and Substance Abuse Services shall submit the survey to the
9 President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate, the Speaker of
10 the Oklahoma House of Representatives, the chairs of the committees
11 with responsibility over common education in both houses of the
12 Legislature, and the chairs of the committees with responsibility
13 over public health in both houses of the Legislature.
14 G. The provisions of this section shall be subject to the
15 availability of federal funding. If federal funding is insufficient
16 to provide the Oklahoma Prevention Needs Assessment Survey to public
17 schools on a biennial basis, administration of the survey shall not
18 be required.
19 H. The Board of Mental Health and Substance Abuse Services and
20 the State Board of Education may promulgate rules as necessary to
21 carry out the provisions of this section.
